<div class="bibEntry"><p class="bib">122. Swindler, Mary Hamilton. Ancient Painting: From the Earliest Times to the Period of Christian Art. New Haven, Connecticut: Yale University Press, 1929. 488 pp. Index, bibl., glossary, endnotes/footnotes, B/W illus., color illus. </p><p class="annot">This survey of ancient civilizations and their painting is arranged chronologically, beginning with the work of the Egyptians and concluding with Roman painting. Swindler considers color throughout the text as it relates to specific paintings and periods. The final chapter on the technical methods and pigments may be useful to those who study palettes used in ancient painting.</p></div>
